snippet.textDisplay: Probably no one will care about this (because it’s about Norwich) but as a Norwich fan, I can’t think of another team in the premier league, except Liverpool, that actually love their players, and we’re bottom of the league. You look at Geordie and he loves Newcastle but he doesn’t love many of the players. Norwich have this love through a connection being built between the board, staff, players and fans. This has been possible because we can’t spunk out 50 mil on a player every other window. Although we are bottom, there is a genuine feeling of positivity around the club, we love the manager, we love the players and I believe we are very lucky to have owners who actually care about the club and the fans
